   <!--
   The above tags are called meta tags and these tags are most of the times essential because they tell browser an overview of what the page
   contains and also gives the browser certain intial values for certain parameters, meta data is machine parsable and is not displayed
   anywhere within the page. Meta data contains information like page description, keywords,author the document, last modified and so on.
   The meta data can be used by browsers on how to display content and so on...

   There are a little few things we need to know about meta tags. The attributes of the meta tag comes mostly in the form of name and content
   or http-equiv and content. The name specifies what the values in the content attribute will be named.For example if we say
   name="keywords" content="HTML,CSS" then it means that HTML, CSS are keywords supplied before hand. This is used mainly for search engines.
   Similarly we may have things like name="description" and associated content, name="author" and associated content and so on. http-equiv has 3
   attributes that we can provide content-type, default-style and refresh. This atribute provides an HTTP header for the value in the
   content attribute.

   In here the attribute http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" tells internet explorer to run in edge mode if possible so that it can render the best
   features...
   -->

